cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with a pattern matching problem and proposes a new algorithmic technique for solving it. This falls under the purview of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS the most likely category.
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the running time of the proposed algorithm and compares it with the previous best algorithm. This involves analyzing the computational complexity of the algorithm, making cs.CC a likely category.
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper uses straight-line programs (SLPs) to represent compressed patterns and texts. SLPs are a common tool in computational geometry, making cs.CG a possible category.
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with a combinatorial problem of pattern matching, which falls under the purview of discrete mathematics. This makes cs.DM a possible category.
5. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) - The paper uses context-free grammars to represent SLPs, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. This makes cs.FL a possible category.
